      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/sqa-mrl2-cpb",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent 2023R1 used under institutional SQA plan covering version control, regression testing, and solver qualification records. SQA documentation meets Gradation 2 requirements for MRL 2: documented test suite with pass/fail records maintained, configuration management applied to all simulation scripts and mesh files. No open defects affecting hemolysis solver pathways."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/code-verification-mrl2-cpb",
      "rationale": "Order-of-accuracy verification performed using manufactured solution on simplified rotating channel geometry representative of impeller passages. Observed order of accuracy 1.87 (theoretical 2.0 for second-order scheme), within acceptable tolerance. Benchmark comparisons against published FDA pump CFD challenge results confirm solver correctness for rotating machinery flows."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/discretization-error-mrl2-cpb",
      "rationale": "Mesh convergence study conducted on three systematically refined meshes (1.2M, 4.8M, 19.2M cells, refinement ratio r=1.587). Grid Convergence Index (GCI) for relative hemolysis index at worst-case operating point: GCI_fine = 18.4%, exceeding the Gradation 2 threshold of ≤10% GCI for the primary quantity of interest. The coarse-to-medium and medium-to-fine RH values were 0.81, 0.74, and 0.71 respectively, indicating the solution has not reached the asymptotic range. Achieved Gradation 1 only: mesh sensitivity documented but GCI criterion not satisfied. This shortfall is the primary basis for the Not Accepted decision."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/test-conditions-mrl2-cpb",
      "rationale": "Experimental test conditions documented to ISO 10993 and ASTM F1841 standards. Five flow-speed operating points (2–6 L/min, 2000–4000 RPM) span the clinical CPB operating envelope. Temperature (37±0.5°C), hematocrit (35±2%), and anticoagulation (heparin 3 U/mL) controlled and recorded. Test conditions replicated in CFD boundary conditions within measurement uncertainty bounds."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/output-comparison-mrl2-cpb",
      "rationale": "Quantitative comparison performed using normalized index of agreement and mean absolute percentage error (MAPE). MAPE for RH index across all 5 operating points: 8.3%. Uncertainty intervals from UQ study (±1σ) encompass all experimental measurements. Trend in worst-case operating point identification consistent between CFD and experiment. Exceeds Gradation 2 requirements; achieves Gradation 3 via systematic uncertainty-inclusive comparison methodology."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/qoi-relevance-mrl2-cpb",
      "rationale": "Primary QoI is the relative hemolysis index (RH) computed via the Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law model integrated along Lagrangian particle trajectories. RH directly maps to the regulatory acceptance criterion (RH < 1 versus predicate). Secondary QoIs (wall shear stress distribution, exposure time histograms) provide mechanistic traceability. QoI selection reviewed and approved by clinical advisor with CPB perfusion expertise."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/validation-relevance-mrl2-cpb",
      "rationale": "Validation activities performed on the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry, which shares impeller topology and operating range with the subject CPB device. Blood analog fluid (glycerin-water, matched viscosity) used in validation experiments with correction factor applied for non-Newtonian effects. Validation operating envelope fully encompasses the COU operating envelope. Validation scenario rated as representative per ASME V&V 40 Table 3 criteria."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/solver-error-mrl2-cpb",
      "rationale": "Iterative convergence monitored via residual norms (all below 1×10⁻⁵) and mass flow balance (imbalance <0.01%). Steady-state MRF simulations confirmed stable convergence over final 500 iterations with RH variation <0.2%. Temporal discretization error not applicable (steady-state formulation). Round-off error assessed as negligible via double-precision arithmetic verification. Achieves Gradation 2, exceeding MRL 2 requirement of Gradation 1."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/use-error-mrl2-cpb",
      "rationale": "Simulation workflow executed under documented standard operating procedure (SOP-CFD-007 Rev C). Independent peer review of mesh setup, boundary condition assignment, and post-processing scripts completed by senior engineer not involved in primary analysis. Two discrepancies identified and corrected during review (incorrect turbulence intensity specification at inlet; particle injection density). Corrected results verified. Achieves Gradation 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/model-form-mrl2-cpb",
      "rationale": "SST k-ω turbulence model selected based on published benchmark performance for rotating blood-contacting device flows (Hariharan et al. 2011, Fraser et al. 2012). Newtonian blood assumption validated against Carreau model comparison showing <3% difference in RH at COU flow rates (>3 L/min, shear rates >100 s⁻¹). Giersiepen-Wurzinger hemolysis model applicability documented with literature support. Model form uncertainty acknowledged and bounded via sensitivity analysis."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/model-inputs-mrl2-cpb",
      "rationale": "All model inputs documented with sources and uncertainty ranges: blood density 1060±5 kg/m³ (ISO 10993), dynamic viscosity 0.0035±0.0003 Pa·s (literature), pump geometry from CMM measurements (±0.05 mm), inlet velocity profiles from PIV measurements. UQ study propagated input uncertainties through model using LHS (n=200 samples). Input uncertainty contribution to RH output uncertainty quantified at ±12% (1σ)."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/test-samples-mrl2-cpb",
      "rationale": "Test samples factor scoped out at MRL 2 for this COU. The validation activity uses a single FDA generic pump geometry as the reference device; sample-to-sample variability assessment is not required at MRL 2 where the model is used for comparative worst-case identification rather than absolute hemolysis prediction across a manufacturing population. This scoping decision is consistent with ASME V&V 40 Table 4 guidance for MRL 2 comparative assessments."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/input-equivalency-mrl2-cpb",
      "rationale": "Equivalency between validation experiment and COU conditions assessed systematically. Geometric similarity: FDA generic pump impeller diameter 52mm vs. subject device 54mm (3.8% difference, within accepted similarity bounds). Reynolds number matching confirmed across operating envelope. Blood analog viscosity correction applied. Hemolysis model coefficients derived from human blood data applicable to COU. Equivalency gaps documented and their impact on RH prediction bounded at ±7% via sensitivity analysis."
    }
